{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftdatahelpers\/livequeryadvancedusage"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers"]]},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This guide collects advanced patterns pulled from the SwiftDataHelpers example","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"app. Use it when you need multiple containers, dynamic queries, or model-layer","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state that stays in sync with SwiftData.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Multiple-Containers-and-Scoped-Queries","type":"heading","text":"Multiple Containers and Scoped Queries","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app uses more than one ","type":"text"},{"code":"ModelContainer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", define them explicitly and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"scope queries to the correct store. A common pattern is to centralize container","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"construction and select between them with an enum.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["enum Database {","    case main","    case privatePersons","","    var container: ModelContainer {","        switch self {","        case .main:","            .main","        case .privatePersons:","            .privatePersons","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When a subtree should read from a non-default container, wrap it in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" so ","type":"text"},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" uses that container’s context.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["LiveQueryBindable(modelContainer: .privatePersons) {","    PrivatePeopleView()","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Dynamic-Predicates-and-Sorting","type":"heading","text":"Dynamic Predicates and Sorting","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When the predicate or sort order depends on view state, initialize the property","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"wrapper in your view’s initializer so it stays consistent with the current","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inputs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct FilteredPeopleList: View {","    private let filter: PersonFilter","    private let sort: PersonSort","","    @LiveQuery private var people: [Person]","","    init(filter: PersonFilter, sort: PersonSort) {","        self.filter = filter","        self.sort = sort","        _people = LiveQuery(predicate: filter.predicate, sort: sort.descriptors)","    }","","    var body: some View {","        ForEach(people) { person in","            Text(person.name)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Using-LiveQuery-in-Observable-Models","type":"heading","text":"Using LiveQuery in Observable Models","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" also works in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" models, which is useful when shared","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state belongs to a feature model instead of a view. Mark the property wrapper","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as ","type":"text"},{"code":"@ObservationIgnored","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so the wrapper itself is not observed, while the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"backing data still updates when SwiftData saves. You can also consume","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"$people.valuesStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for async snapshot handling.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@MainActor","@Observable","final class PeopleFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery var people: [Person]","","    @ObservationIgnored","    private var valuesTask: Task<Void, Never>?","","    func observePeople() {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","        valuesTask = Task {","            for await snapshot in $people.valuesStream {","                print(\"People count: \\(snapshot.count)\")","            }","        }","    }","","    deinit {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Background-Writes-with-ModelActor","type":"heading","text":"Background Writes with @ModelActor","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When writes happen on a background model actor, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@LiveQuery"},{"type":"text","text":" still refreshes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because SwiftData posts save notifications on the container."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@ModelActor","actor PersonImporter {","    func importPeople(_ seeds: [PersonSeed]) throws {","        for seed in seeds {","            let person = Person(id: UUID(), name: seed.name, age: seed.age)","            modelContext.insert(person)","        }","","        try modelContext.save()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Environment-Specific-Containers-for-Tests-and-Previews","type":"heading","text":"Environment-Specific Containers for Tests and Previews","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example app uses Dependencies "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" to build live containers in the app"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and in-memory containers for tests and previews. This keeps "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@LiveQuery"},{"type":"text","text":" fast"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and deterministic in non-live environments."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["